byline.original: By ALISSA J. RUBIN and MAÏA de la BAUME

abstract: Preliminary results for local elections in France suggest voter frustration with governing Socialist Party; center-right parties take 30 percent of vote and far-right National Front takes 25 percent, significant increase from similar elections in 2011.
lead_paragraph: Exit polls and early returns in the first round of voting indicated dissatisfaction with the Socialist Party of President François Hollande.

headline.main: France’s Conservative Parties Show Strength and National Front Gains in Local Elections
headline.print_headline: Local Voting Favors Right in France

snippet: Exit polls and early returns in the first round of voting indicated dissatisfaction with the Socialist Party of President François Hollande.
